My two tween daughters really love this show.  The show features Carly, a girl in her early teens produces her own web show with the help of two friends: wild and crazy Sam (as in Samantha) and the boy next door, Freddie.  Their antics on the webshow are entertaining to watch, but the real fun comes from watching these fairly typical teenagers interact with one another and their classmates.

The absolute highlight is Carly's older brother, Spencer, with whom she lives.  He is hilarious as he tries to walk the line between cool older brother and responsible guardian.

This show may be written for tweens, but it is funny enough for adults.  And a good clean show that the whole family can enjoy is a rare find indeed!
